cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about facial landmark tracking, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new algorithm for incremental learning in the cascaded regression framework, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities in facial landmark tracking, which involves understanding and modeling human faces, a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm is designed for real-time tracking, which involves controlling and monitoring physical systems, a topic that falls under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm using performance metrics, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
